data.comment: The match is underway at Roazhon Park.
At Roazhon Park, Monaco are penalized for being offside.
In the minute 1, It's a goal kick for the home team in Rennes.
Monaco awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Throw-in Monaco.
In the minute 4, Rennes attack but Martin Terrier's header doesn't find the target.
Jerome Miguelgorry awards Monaco a goal kick.
Ball safe as Monaco is awarded a throw-in in their half.
In the minute 5, Free kick for Rennes in their own half.
Throw-in for Rennes in the half of Monaco.
Jerome Miguelgorry awards the away team a throw-in.
In the minute 8, Monaco have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
Monaco push upfield and Axel Disasi gets his head to the ball. The attempt is cleared by an alert Rennes defence.
Throw-in for Monaco at Roazhon Park.
In the minute 10, Corner awarded to Monaco.
Goal kick for Rennes at Roazhon Park.
Throw-in for Rennes in their own half.
In the minute 14, Ball safe as Monaco is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Monaco awarded a free kick in their own half.
Monaco are pushing forward but Youssouf Fofana's finish is wide of the goal.
In the minute 15, Rennes have a goal kick.
Monaco have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
Ball goes out of play for a Rennes goal kick.
In the minute 17, Rennes awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Rennes's Eduardo Camavinga gets in a shot but it is blocked by a Monaco defender.
Corner awarded to Rennes.
In the minute 20, Martin Terrier (Rennes) gets in a strike but the shot is blocked by a defender.
Corner awarded to Rennes.
Rennes have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
In the minute 24, Throw-in Rennes.
Jerome Miguelgorry signals a free kick to Rennes in their own half.
Corner awarded to Rennes.
In the minute 28, Monaco push forward at Roazhon Park and Aurelien Tchouameni gets in a strike. This is blocked, however, by a determined Rennes defence.
Monaco have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
Monaco take a 0-1 lead thanks to Wissam Ben Yedder.
In the minute 30, Jerome Miguelgorry awards the home team a throw-in.
Monaco have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
Corner awarded to Monaco.
In the minute 33, Rennes to take a throw-in in Monaco territory.
Jerome Miguelgorry signals a free kick to Rennes just outside Monaco's area.
Can Rennes get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Monaco's half?
In the minute 35, The match at Roazhon Park has been interrupted briefly for a check on Faitout Maouassa, who is down injured.
Faitout Maouassa has recovered and rejoins the match in Rennes.
Monaco awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 38, A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Throw-in for Rennes in their own half.
Faitout Maouassa is writhing in pain and play has been suspended for a few moments.
In the minute 41, Julien Stephan (Rennes) is making a first change, with Adrien Truffert replacing the possibly injured Faitout Maouassa.
Monaco have a goal kick.
Free kick for Rennes in the half of Monaco.
In the minute 44, Throw-in for Rennes at Roazhon Park.
Monaco are too eager and fall into an offside trap.
Jerome Miguelgorry signals a Rennes throw-in in Monaco's half.
In the minute 45, Jerome Miguelgorry will wait an extra 3 minutes before blowing the whistle to end the 1st half.
Jerome Miguelgorry signals a free kick to Monaco in their own half.
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
In the minute 45, Corner awarded to Monaco.
Free kick for Rennes in their own half.
Important block from the Monaco defence as Benjamin Bourigeaud fires in a strike for Rennes.
In the minute 45, Rennes have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
The first-half is over.
The second-half is now underway.
In the minute 46, Monaco are caught offside.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Rennes.
Free kick for Rennes in their own half.
In the minute 48, Throw-in Monaco.
Martin Terrier of Rennes gets in a strike, but is off target.
Jerome Miguelgorry awards Monaco a goal kick.
In the minute 51, In Rennes a free kick has been awarded the home team.
Monaco awarded a free kick in their own half.
Goal kick for Monaco at Roazhon Park.
In the minute 54, Ball goes out of play for a Rennes goal kick.
Throw-in for Monaco in the half of Rennes.
Ball goes out of play for a Monaco goal kick.
In the minute 57, Monaco have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
Corner awarded to Monaco.
Monaco are coming forward and Wissam Ben Yedder gets in a strike, it misses the target, however.
In the minute 57, It's a goal kick for the home team in Rennes.
Julien Stephan is making the team's second substitution at Roazhon Park with Romain Del Castillo replacing Raphinha.
Jerome Miguelgorry signals a Rennes throw-in in Monaco's half.
In the minute 60, Rennes have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
Jerome Miguelgorry signals a free kick to Monaco in their own half.
Nayef Aguerd is down and play has been interrupted for a few moments.
In the minute 61, Play has been interrupted briefly in Rennes to check on Axel Disasi, who is grimacing with pain.
Axel Disasi for Monaco is back on the field again.
Nayef Aguerd is back on the pitch.
In the minute 63, Corner awarded to Rennes.
Goal kick for Monaco at Roazhon Park.
Rennes awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 64, Jerome Miguelgorry signals a free kick to Rennes.
Ball safe as Monaco is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Benjamin Bourigeaud hits the post! Very nearly a goal there for Rennes!
In the minute 66, Rennes to take a throw-in in Monaco territory.
Throw-in for Monaco at Roazhon Park.
Can Rennes capitalize from this dangerous free kick?
In the minute 68, Monaco's Axel Disasi has been booked in Rennes.
Rennes's Benjamin Bourigeaud is on target but unsuccessful.
Throw-in for Rennes in their own half.
In the minute 71, Free kick Monaco.
Willem Geubbels is replacing Cesc Fabregas for Monaco at Roazhon Park.
In Rennes Monaco attack through Djibril Sidibe. The finish is off target, however.
In the minute 73, Rennes have a goal kick.
Monaco awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Jerome Miguelgorry awards the home team a throw-in.
In the minute 74, Play has been temporarily suspended for attention to Nayef Aguerd for Rennes who is writhing in pain on the pitch.
Nayef Aguerd is back on his feet again.
Free kick Rennes.
In the minute 76, Willem Geubbels is booked for the away team.
Free kick for Rennes in their own half.
Sehrou Guirassy (Rennes) is first to the ball but his header is off-target.
In the minute 79, Jerome Miguelgorry awards Monaco a goal kick.
The home team replace Benjamin Bourigeaud with Jonas Martin.
The home team have replaced Eduardo Camavinga with Flavien Tait. This is the fourth substitution made today by Julien Stephan.
In the minute 81, Steven Nzonzi (Rennes) levels the match at 1-1 with a header.
That's a fine assist from Adrien Truffert.
Monaco make their second substitution with Henry Onyekuru replacing Wissam Ben Yedder.
In the minute 84, Jerome Miguelgorry signals a free kick to Monaco in their own half.
Can Monaco get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Rennes's half?
In Rennes a free kick has been awarded the away team.
In the minute 86, Jerome Miguelgorry signals a free kick to Rennes in their own half.
Rennes's Martin Terrier gets his shot away but it misses the target.
Jerome Miguelgorry awards Monaco a goal kick.
In the minute 87, Can Rennes get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Monaco's half?
Throw-in for Monaco in the half of Rennes.
Free kick for Monaco in the half of Rennes.
In the minute 89, Monaco have a goal kick.
Niko Kovac (Monaco) is making a third substitution, with Gelson Martins replacing Kevin Volland.
Rennes have been awarded a corner by Jerome Miguelgorry.
5 minutes of injury time will be added to the 2nd half.
Corner awarded to Rennes.
A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
Corner awarded to Monaco.
Ball goes out of play for a Rennes goal kick.
Monaco awarded a free kick in their own half.
It's 2-1 as the referee blows for full-time.
Goal! Adrien Truffert gives Rennes a 2-1 lead in Rennes.
Martin Terrier instrumental with a fine assist.
Guillermo Maripan is replacing Sofiane Diop for the away team.
Stevan Jovetic is on a sub for Aurelien Tchouameni for Monaco.
Martin Terrier (Rennes) gets a yellow card.
